```go
}
```

<a name="TLSExtensionWriter"></a>
## type [TLSExtensionWriter](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_tls_extensions.go#L102-L111>)

TLSExtensionWriter is an interface allowing a TLS extension to be auto\-constucted/recovered by reading in a byte stream.

```go
type TLSExtensionWriter interface {
    TLSExtension

    // Write writes the extension data as a byte slice, up to len(b) bytes from b.
    // It returns the number of bytes written (0 <= n <= len(b)) and any error encountered.
    //
    // The implementation MUST NOT silently drop data if consumed less than len(b) bytes,
    // instead, it MUST return an error.
    Write(b []byte) (n int, err error)
}
```

<a name="TLSExtensionsJSONUnmarshaler"></a>
## type [TLSExtensionsJSONUnmarshaler](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_clienthello_json.go#L87-L91>)



```go
type TLSExtensionsJSONUnmarshaler struct {
    AllowUnknownExt bool // if set, unknown extensions will be added as GenericExtension, without recovering ext payload
    UseRealPSK      bool // if set, PSK extension will be real PSK extension, otherwise it will be fake PSK extension
    // contains filtered or unexported fields
}
```

<a name="TransportParameter"></a>
## type [TransportParameter](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_quic_transport_parameters.go#L59-L62>)

TransportParameter represents a QUIC transport parameter.

Caller will write the following to the wire:

```
var b []byte
b = quicvarint.Append(b, ID())
b = quicvarint.Append(b, len(Value()))
b = append(b, Value())
```

Therefore Value\(\) should return the exact bytes to be written to the wire AFTER the length field, i.e., the bytes MAY be a Variable Length Integer per RFC depending on the type of the transport parameter, but MUST NOT including the length field unless the parameter is defined so.

```go
type TransportParameter interface {
    ID() uint64
    Value() []byte
}
```

<a name="TransportParameters"></a>
## type [TransportParameters](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_quic_transport_parameters.go#L35>)



```go
type TransportParameters []TransportParameter
```

<a name="TransportParameters.Marshal"></a>
### func \(TransportParameters\) [Marshal](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_quic_transport_parameters.go#L37>)

```go
func (tps TransportParameters) Marshal() []byte
```

### func \(\*UConn\) [ApplyPreset](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_parrots.go#L2621>)

```go
func (uconn *UConn) ApplyPreset(p *ClientHelloSpec) error
```

ApplyPreset should only be used in conjunction with HelloCustom to apply custom specs. Fields of TLSExtensions that are slices/pointers are shared across different connections with same ClientHelloSpec. It is advised to use different specs and avoid any shared state.

<a name="UConn.BuildHandshakeState"></a>
### func \(\*UConn\) [BuildHandshakeState](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_conn.go#L91>)

```go
func (uconn *UConn) BuildHandshakeState() error
```

BuildHandshakeState behavior varies based on ClientHelloID and whether it was already called before. If HelloGolang:

```
[only once] make default ClientHello and overwrite existing state
```

If any other mimicking ClientHelloID is used:

```
[only once] make ClientHello based on ID and overwrite existing state
[each call] apply uconn.Extensions config to internal crypto/tls structures
[each call] marshal ClientHello.
```

BuildHandshakeState is automatically called before uTLS performs handshake, and should only be called explicitly to inspect/change fields of default/mimicked ClientHello. With the excpetion of session ticket and psk extensions, which cannot be changed after calling BuildHandshakeState, all other fields can be modified.

<a name="UConn.BuildHandshakeStateWithoutSession"></a>
### func \(\*UConn\) [BuildHandshakeStateWithoutSession](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_conn.go#L99>)

```go
func (uconn *UConn) BuildHandshakeStateWithoutSession() error
```

BuildHandshakeStateWithoutSession is the same as BuildHandshakeState, but does not set the session. This is only useful when you want to inspect the ClientHello before setting the session manually through SetSessionTicketExtension or SetPSKExtension. BuildHandshakeState is automatically called before uTLS performs handshake.

<a name="UConn.HandshakeContext"></a>
### func \(\*UConn\) [HandshakeContext](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_conn.go#L311>)

```go
func (c *UConn) HandshakeContext(ctx context.Context) error
```

HandshakeContext runs the client or server handshake protocol if it has not yet been run.

The provided Context must be non\-nil. If the context is canceled before the handshake is complete, the handshake is interrupted and an error is returned. Once the handshake has completed, cancellation of the context will not affect the connection.

<a name="UConn.SetTLSVers"></a>
### func \(\*UConn\) [SetTLSVers](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_conn.go#L751>)

```go
func (uconn *UConn) SetTLSVers(minTLSVers, maxTLSVers uint16, specExtensions []TLSExtension) error
```

SetTLSVers sets min and max TLS version in all appropriate places. Function will use first non\-zero version parsed in following order:

1. Provided minTLSVers, maxTLSVers
2. specExtensions may have SupportedVersionsExtension
3. \[default\] min = TLS 1.0, max = TLS 1.2

Error is only returned if things are in clearly undesirable state to help user fix them.

<a name="UtlsPaddingExtension"></a>
## type [UtlsPaddingExtension](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/u_tls_extensions.go#L988-L995>)

UtlsPaddingExtension implements padding \(21\)

```go
type UtlsPaddingExtension struct {
    PaddingLen int
    WillPad    bool // set to false to disable extension

    // Functor for deciding on padding length based on unpadded ClientHello length.
    // If willPad is false, then this extension should not be included.
    GetPaddingLen func(clientHelloUnpaddedLen int) (paddingLen int, willPad bool)
}
```

# testenv

```go
import "github.com/refraction-networking/utls/testenv"
```

Package testenv provides information about what functionality is available in different testing environments run by the Go team.

It is an internal package because these details are specific to the Go team's test setup \(on build.golang.org\) and not fundamental to tests in general.

## Index

- [Constants](<#constants>)

## Variables

<a name="Sigquit"></a>Sigquit is the signal to send to kill a hanging subprocess. On Unix we send SIGQUIT, but on non\-Unix we only have os.Kill.

```go
var Sigquit = os.Kill
```

<a name="Builder"></a>
## func [Builder](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L90>)

```go
func Builder() string
```

Builder reports the name of the builder running this test \(for example, "linux\-amd64" or "windows\-386\-gce"\). If the test is not running on the build infrastructure, Builder returns the empty string.

<a name="CPUIsSlow"></a>
## func [CPUIsSlow](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L350>)

```go
func CPUIsSlow() bool
```

CPUIsSlow reports whether the CPU running the test is suspected to be slow.

<a name="CanInternalLink"></a>
## func [CanInternalLink](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L257>)

```go
func CanInternalLink() bool
```

CanInternalLink reports whether the current system can link programs with internal linking. \(This is the opposite of cmd/internal/sys.MustLinkExternal. Keep them in sync.\)

<a name="CleanCmdEnv"></a>
## func [CleanCmdEnv](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L330>)

```go
func CleanCmdEnv(cmd *exec.Cmd) *exec.Cmd
```

CleanCmdEnv will fill cmd.Env with the environment, excluding certain variables that could modify the behavior of the Go tools such as GODEBUG and GOTRACEBACK.

<a name="GoTool"></a>
## func [GoTool](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L157>)

```go
func GoTool() (string, error)
```

GoTool reports the path to the Go tool.

<a name="GoToolPath"></a>
## func [GoToolPath](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L141>)

```go
func GoToolPath(t testing.TB) string
```

GoToolPath reports the path to the Go tool. It is a convenience wrapper around GoTool. If the tool is unavailable GoToolPath calls t.Skip. If the tool should be available and isn't, GoToolPath calls t.Fatal.

<a name="RunWithTimeout"></a>
## func [RunWithTimeout](<https://github.com/refraction-networking/utls/blob/master/testenv/testenv.go#L372>)

```go
func RunWithTimeout(t testing.TB, cmd *exec.Cmd) ([]byte, error)
```

RunWithTimeout runs cmd and returns its combined output. If the subprocess exits with a non\-zero status, it will log that status and return a non\-nil error, but this is not considered fatal.


SkipIfShortAndSlow skips t if \-short is set and the CPU running the test is suspected to be slow.

\(This is useful for CPU\-intensive tests that otherwise complete quickly.\)

## Constants

<a name="Min"></a>taken from the QUIC draft

```go
const (
    // Min is the minimum value allowed for a QUIC varint.
    Min = 0

    // Max is the maximum allowed value for a QUIC varint (2^62-1).
    Max = maxVarInt8
)
```

## Constants

<a name="DefaultAckDelayExponent"></a>DefaultAckDelayExponent is the default ack delay exponent

```go
const DefaultAckDelayExponent = 3
```

<a name="DefaultActiveConnectionIDLimit"></a>DefaultActiveConnectionIDLimit is the default active connection ID limit

```go
const DefaultActiveConnectionIDLimit = 2
```

<a name="DefaultMaxAckDelay"></a>DefaultMaxAckDelay is the default max\_ack\_delay

```go
const DefaultMaxAckDelay = 25 * time.Millisecond
```

<a name="InvalidPacketLimitAES"></a>InvalidPacketLimitAES is the maximum number of packets that we can fail to decrypt when using AEAD\_AES\_128\_GCM or AEAD\_AES\_265\_GCM.

```go
const InvalidPacketLimitAES = 1 << 52
```

<a name="InvalidPacketLimitChaCha"></a>InvalidPacketLimitChaCha is the maximum number of packets that we can fail to decrypt when using AEAD\_CHACHA20\_POLY1305.

```go
const InvalidPacketLimitChaCha = 1 << 36
```

<a name="MaxAckDelayExponent"></a>MaxAckDelayExponent is the maximum ack delay exponent

```go
const MaxAckDelayExponent = 20
```

<a name="MaxByteCount"></a>MaxByteCount is the maximum value of a ByteCount

```go
const MaxByteCount = ByteCount(1<<62 - 1)
```

<a name="MaxConnIDLen"></a>MaxConnIDLen is the maximum length of the connection ID

```go
const MaxConnIDLen = 20
```

<a name="MaxLargePacketBufferSize"></a>MaxLargePacketBufferSize is used when using GSO

```go
const MaxLargePacketBufferSize = 20 * 1024
```

<a name="MaxMaxAckDelay"></a>MaxMaxAckDelay is the maximum max\_ack\_delay

```go
const MaxMaxAckDelay = (1<<14 - 1) * time.Millisecond
```

<a name="MaxPacketBufferSize"></a>MaxPacketBufferSize maximum packet size of any QUIC packet, based on ethernet's max size, minus the IP and UDP headers. IPv6 has a 40 byte header, UDP adds an additional 8 bytes. This is a total overhead of 48 bytes. Ethernet's max packet size is 1500 bytes, 1500 \- 48 = 1452.

```go
const MaxPacketBufferSize = 1452
```

<a name="MinConnectionIDLenInitial"></a>MinConnectionIDLenInitial is the minimum length of the destination connection ID on an Initial packet.

```go
const MinConnectionIDLenInitial = 8
```

<a name="MinInitialPacketSize"></a>MinInitialPacketSize is the minimum size an Initial packet is required to have.

```go
const MinInitialPacketSize = 1200
```

<a name="MinStatelessResetSize"></a>MinStatelessResetSize is the minimum size of a stateless reset packet that we send

```go
const MinStatelessResetSize = 1 + 20 + 4 + 1 + 16 /* token */
```

<a name="MinUnknownVersionPacketSize"></a>MinUnknownVersionPacketSize is the minimum size a packet with an unknown version needs to have in order to trigger a Version Negotiation packet.

```go
const MinUnknownVersionPacketSize = MinInitialPacketSize
```
